{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01Drpsn6oGYWwCe9FYEt7Wzw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011QbGyMSzc4yu81CKEgcUWd","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The generated reply references specific points from the incoming email rather than producing a generic response.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"A mock LLM returning pre-written text with references would not catch the real failure: that the production LLM doesn't reference specific points due to poor prompting, truncated context, or task misunderstanding. The correctness boundary is the real LLM's behavior when given the full email thread and prompt. Only a call to the real LLM can verify this.","test_description":"Call the real LLM with a real email thread containing specific details (e.g., 'client asked about Q3 budget' and 'mentioned staffing concerns'). Assert that the generated draft directly addresses those specific points—not generic boilerplate—by checking for references to concrete details from the email.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The factual consistency check flags claims in the draft that contradict entries in the knowledge base.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"A Unit test with a mocked KB that always returns 'contradiction found' would not test the actual matching logic. To catch real failures—broken claim extraction, failed KB lookups, or faulty contradiction detection—you need to test the full consistency-check pipeline with real or realistic KB data and actual claims. The failure boundary crosses multiple modules (claim extraction → KB lookup → comparison).","test_description":"Create a test KB with known entries (e.g., 'Q3 revenue: $4.5M'). Generate a draft containing a conflicting claim ('Q3 revenue was $5M'). Run the factual consistency checker on the draft and assert the contradiction is flagged in the result.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When the knowledge base has no relevant entries, the draft includes a disclaimer rather than fabricating facts.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"A Unit test with a mocked LLM returning a static disclaimer would not catch the core failure: that the real LLM ignores the 'add disclaimer' instruction and hallucinates facts instead. Honesty vs. fabrication is an LLM behavior property that cannot be mocked—it depends on the real model's reasoning and instruction-following. Only calling the real LLM with an empty KB reveals if it respects the prompt.","test_description":"Call the real LLM with a draft request on a topic outside the KB (e.g., 'respond about future market predictions') when the KB is empty or has no matching entries. Assert that the output includes an explicit disclaimer (e.g., 'I don't have information on this topic') and contains no fabricated facts presented as verified information.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The approval workflow blocks sending until the user explicitly approves — no draft is sent automatically.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is a control-flow failure: send() is called when it shouldn't be. Mock the send function and the approval check; call the workflow without approval granted. Assert send() is never called. This local test of the workflow function with mocked dependencies catches the failure without needing full integration wiring.","test_description":"Unit test: mock the send() function and approval handler. Call the workflow function with approval returning false/not-approved. Assert the mocked send() is never invoked. Verify that only after approval transitions to true can sending proceed.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.55,"Integration":0.3,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence — read thread, generate draft, check facts, present for approval — works end-to-end for a real email thread.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This behavior requires multiple real agentic steps (LLM draft generation, and depending on implementation, potentially LLM-based fact checking) to execute in sequence and integrate correctly. Integration tests of individual components would miss failures at the seams: e.g., claims not extracted properly for the consistency check, or the approval gate failing after a successful fact check. Workflow-level testing ensures the full agentic pipeline executes and hands off state correctly.","test_description":"End-to-end test with a real email thread containing specific references. Invoke the full pipeline: read thread → call real LLM to generate draft → run factual consistency check → verify draft is presented for approval without auto-sending. Assert each step succeeds, the draft references the email, facts are checked, and no send occurs until approval.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.7}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":13334,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"92032331-1a7f-4e7d-b8d5-85d9fea1e6cc","uuid":"47033dad-e101-4536-aabc-b6523f054a38"}
